festival.introText:
110 Above (previously Lainfest) is a completely independent three day music festival. The festival is held in Twycross with the exact site being 110m above sea level where Gopsall Hall once stood.

Capacity is carefully limited to give attendees a chilled out, intimate and stress-free experience that cannot be gained from larger commercial events.

faqs.question: When is 110 Above Presents: OTHR Festival 2023?
faqs.answer: 110 Above Presents: OTHR Festival takes place Thursday 10th August - Monday 14th August 2023.

faqs.question: How to get to 110 Above Presents: OTHR Festival
faqs.answer:
BY CAR

Gopsall Hall Farm, Twycross, Leicestershire, CV9 3QJ. If you bring a car you must must purchase a parking pass in advance.

 

BY TRAIN

The nearest station to the festival site is Atherstone (10 miles). More frequent services run to Nuneaton (12 miles) and Tamworth (14 miles). A taxi from these stations will cost approximately £25. A cheaper way is to book a shuttle bus ticket in advance.

 

BY SHUTTLE BUS

The festival are offering transfers from Nuneaton train station on Thursday and Friday.  The minibuses will depart Nuneaton train station at 12 noon on Thursday and Friday and return on Monday, leaving the festival site at 10.30am (approximate arrival to Nuneaton is 11.30am).  Tickets can be purchased in the Extras section of the festival website.

faqs.question: Is there camping available at 110 Above Presents: OTHR Festival?
faqs.answer: Yes, the festival has many onsite camping and glamping options available including family camping, caravans/motorhomes with electric hookup and general.

faqs.question: How much are 110 Above Presents: OTHR Festival tickets?
faqs.answer: Ticket prices vary, please see https://www.110above.com/ for further information.

faqs.question: Where is 110 Above Presents: OTHR Festival?
faqs.answer: 110 Above Presents: OTHR Festival is located at Gopsall Hall Farm, Twycross, Leicestershire, CV9 3QJ.

faqs.question: Are there any age restrictions at 110 Above Presents: OTHR Festival?
faqs.answer: No, families are welcome at the festival. All under 18s must be accompanied by a parent/guardian over 18. The festival is free for under 13s (12 and under).
